I see this

/Applications/Xcode-beta.app/Contents/Developer


I also have the latest RC of the Studio....all seems to be installed properly...yet studio will not recognize anything.....

Help

comments.body:
This is due to xcode 11 being new and we only started supporting it recently. Can you try SDK 8.2?

And can you also run the latest CLI RC in combination with that?

{code}
appc ti sdk install --branch master 8.2.0.v20190731191122
[sudo] npm install -g appcelerator@4.2.14-3
appc use 7.1.0-24
{code}
Hello [~peterladis], Did you tried with the 8.2.x master releases? follow Rene's guide? Let us know if you still have the issue with the Xcode 11 beta version. Thanks.

Hello!

Hope you are doing fine today.

Would you please reply us regarding previous reviews? We are looking forward to your response.

I think this is caused by DAEMON-282/CLI-1363 we're currently planning to release an RC this week that will fix this. Note you can build from the CLI to an iOS 13 sim, this is just in the detection logic that powers Studio
Hello [~peterladis], Can you please follow up here? Are you able to run into iOS simulator through the terminal? Thanks.
